Use the standard library
This is how to order_by_points of nums:
   Remember that n is nums's length
   Remember that arr is []
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that x is item i in nums
      Remember that ax is abs of x
      Remember that s is tostring of ax
      Remember that points is 0
      Remember that j is 0
      Do this s's length times:
         Remember that c is item j in s
         Remember that points is sum of points and (diff of c and 48)
         Increase j
      End do
      Add arr to {"value": x, "points": points}
      Increase i
   End do

   Remember that pass is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that i is 0
      Remember that limit is diff of n and 1
      Do this limit times:
         Remember that j is sum of i and 1
         Remember that a is item i in arr
         Remember that b is item j in arr
         Remember that ap is item "points" in a
         Remember that bp is item "points" in b
         Remember that av is item "value" in a
         Remember that bv is item "value" in b
         Remember that swap is 0
         When ap is more than bp, then:
            Remember that swap is 1
         End when
         When ap is bp, then:
            When av is more than bv, then:
               Remember that swap is 1
            End when
         End when
         When swap is 1, then:
            Remember that tmp is item i in arr
            Remember that item i in arr is item j in arr
            Remember that item j in arr is tmp
         End when
         Increase i
      End do
      Increase pass
   End do

   Remember that result is []
   Remember that k is 0
   Do this n times:
      Add result to item "value" in item k in arr
      Increase k
   End do
   The answer is result
Now you know